author: kevan
msg: Some spec 'extensions' snuck into the javamail spec since 1.0. BodyPart.setParent() cannot be public. I've given it package-level access which mimics Sun's api implementation. MimeUtility.fold(...) cannot be public. It wasn't used. So, I've deleted. Finally, the AddressParser class cannot be public. I've given it package-level access.
